# =============================================================================
# Autonomous Drug Repurposing Platform — .gitignore
# =============================================================================
# v118 IN-053 ROOT FIX (Teammate 16): the previous .gitignore was a partial
# list that ignored ``phase1/processed_data/`` but NOT ``phase1/raw_data/``
# (10-100GB of downloaded biomedical data), NOT ``logs/`` (audit JSONL
# files), NOT ``.airflow_home/`` (Airflow scheduler state), NOT ``*.db``
# (SQLite fallback DBs), NOT recursive ``**/*.egg-info/``. An operator
# running ``git add .`` after a full pipeline run would commit tens of GB
# of regenerable artifacts. GitHub rejects pushes > 100MB. The fix below
# uses globs that cover ALL output directories (output_v100, output_real_run,
# output_full_platform, dev_output_v100, output_v118, etc.) and ALL SQLite
# DBs (phase1.db, frontend/dev.db, etc.).
# =============================================================================

# ─── Python bytecode & build artifacts ──────────────────────────────────────
*.pyc
__pycache__/
*.pyo
*.pyd
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.tox/
.coverage
htmlcov/
coverage.xml
*.egg-info/
**/*.egg-info/
*.egg
build/
dist/

# ─── Virtual environments ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/

# ─── Pipeline outputs (regenerable, do not commit) ──────────────────────────
# v91 + v118: glob ``output_*/`` covers output_v100, output_real_run,
# output_full_platform, dev_output_v100, output_v118, etc. Also keep the
# explicit entries for backwards compat with tooling that globs .gitignore.
output_*/
output_v100/
dev_output_v100/
rl/output/
checkpoints/
graph_transformer/retrain_triggered.json

# ─── Phase 1 data directories (downloaded biomedical data, 10-100GB) ────────
phase1/processed_data/
phase1/raw_data/

# ─── Logs & audit JSONL (regenerable, do not commit) ────────────────────────
logs/
**/logs/audit/*.jsonl
**/logs/audit/*.jsonl.lock
**/logs/transformations/*.jsonl
# v124 P2-043 REAL ROOT FIX: prevent future audit-log backup files from
# being committed. The previous "fix" kept corrupted backup files
# (bridge_fallbacks.jsonl.p2-043-pre-purge-bak,
# v109_archived/bridge_fallbacks.jsonl.v108_pre_fix, etc.) tracked in
# git, meaning anyone who cloned the repo inherited 909 lines of
# nonsensical thread_3/write_NN test-pollution entries. These patterns
# catch ALL backup-file naming schemes so the corruption can't recur.
**/logs/audit/*.bak
**/logs/audit/*.pre-purge-bak
**/logs/audit/*-pre-purge-bak
**/logs/audit/*.v*_pre_fix
**/logs/audit/v*_archived/
**/logs/audit/**.bak

# ─── Airflow state (scheduler, db, logs) ────────────────────────────────────
.airflow_home/
airflow.db
airflow.cfg
airflow-webserver.pid
airflow.cfg*

# ─── SQLite DBs (frontend dev DB, phase1 fallback DB, etc.) ─────────────────
*.db
*.db-journal
*.db-shm
*.db-wal
frontend/dev.db
frontend/prisma/*.db
frontend/prisma/prisma/
frontend/db/

# ─── Frontend build artifacts & deps ────────────────────────────────────────
frontend/.next/
frontend/node_modules/
frontend/.next/standalone/
frontend/.next/cache/
frontend/dev.log
frontend/server.log
frontend/playwright-report/
frontend/test-results/
frontend/coverage/

# ─── Environment files (NEVER commit real secrets) ──────────────────────────
# v116 IN-001/BE-004/P1-001 ROOT FIX: root .env holds REAL secrets (Fernet
# key, DB passwords, API keys). It MUST NOT be committed. .env.example is
# the committed template with placeholders only.
# v118 IN-052 ROOT FIX (Teammate 16): the .env.* glob catches ALL .env
# variants (.env.staging, .env.production, .env.development, etc.). The
# !.env.example + !**/.env.example negations allow the example templates
# (with placeholders only) to be committed.
.env
.env.local
.env.*
!.env.example
!**/.env.example

# ─── Docker Compose secrets directory (IN-088) ──────────────────────────────
# The secrets/ directory holds file-based secrets mounted into containers
# via the compose ``secrets:`` block (postgres_password.txt,
# neo4j_password.txt, airflow_fernet_key.txt, etc.). These files contain
# REAL credentials and MUST NEVER be committed to git.
secrets/
secrets/*.txt

# ─── IDE / editor / OS files ────────────────────────────────────────────────
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ─── Bun (binary lockfile not diffable) ─────────────────────────────────────
bun.lockb
